{{!
    @template mod_fastpix/player_wrapper

    The player mount wrapper + segmented coverage-bar card. Extracted from
    view.mustache so it can be rendered BOTH server-side (view.php → renderer)
    AND client-side (processing_state_poller renders this partial via
    core/templates when the asset goes ready, swapping it into the processing
    region with no full-page reload).

    The mount payload (view_state_player::to_player_payload) supplies every var
    used here, so this partial renders identically in either path. There is no
    inline-JS block here; the player AMD module's init/mount is triggered by the
    caller (view.php via js_call_amd, or the poller via the player module).

    NOTE — never write a curly-brace pair inside this comment. Mustache treats
    the first closing brace pair it finds as the comment terminator, so any such
    token leaks the rest of the comment as literal text at the top of the
    rendered HTML. That stray leading text breaks the client-side swap: Moodle's
    Templates/replaceNodeContents hands it to jQuery, which parses the leading
    words as a CSS selector and throws "unrecognized expression".

    The wrapper carries data-* attributes (the documented watch_tracker context
    contract, CC4). They are harmless — the AMD player reads from the payload,
    not these attrs — but preserved so existing consumers keep working.

    Player attribute names are pinned to the @fastpix/fp-player web component
    public surface (CC9). Renaming without reading upstream docs is a CC9
    violation — the player silently renders an inert black box if attrs drift.

    Context variables:
      * playback_id              string
      * playback_token           string  (DRM JWT)
      * expires_at_ts            int     (unix seconds)
      * drm_required             bool
      * accent_color             string|null
      * default_show_captions    bool
      * activity_name            string
      * activity_id              int
      * cm_id                    int
      * asset_id                 int
      * session_token            string
      * no_skip_required         bool
      * initial_coverage_percent int
      * completion_watch_percent int
      * current_position         float
      * asset_duration_seconds   int
      * initial_intervals_json   string
      * has_completed            bool
      * drm_token                string
      * intro_html               string  (formatted activity intro; may be empty)
      * (completed-indicator var)  has_completed (initial visibility only)

    DESCRIPTION (intro_html) — rendered BELOW the player + completed pill, inside
    the .mod_fastpix-lede card, ONLY when non-empty (the section wrap suppresses
    an empty card). format_module_intro already filters/sanitises the teacher's
    intro, so it is emitted via the raw triple-brace output — the standard Moodle
    pattern for pre-formatted intro HTML. Living here (not in view.php) means the
    description appears with the player in BOTH the server render and the in-place
    processing→player poller swap, and is naturally absent on processing/error.

    COMPLETED INDICATOR — the single watch-status UI, and the ONLY thing it ever
    shows is "Completed". It is absolutely positioned in the top-right corner
    INSIDE this wrapper (the wrapper is position:relative, set in styles.css),
    overlaid on the video so it never collides with the player's bottom control
    bar. There is NO background box/pill/backdrop — just the inline-SVG check +
    "Completed" text, made legible over the dark video with a text-shadow.

    Visibility is binary: hidden until completion. On first paint the indicator is
    hidden unless has_completed is true (the .is-complete class on the root node
    toggles it; default hidden). When the coverage tracker in player.js crosses
    the completion threshold it adds .is-complete (sticky — never removed). The
    tracker only toggles that class; it never rebuilds the node or constructs icon
    markup. The check is INLINE SVG (zero font dependency) so a missing icon-font
    glyph can never render a square. data-region="fastpix-status" is the single
    AMD hook. The carrier data-threshold/data-asset-duration on this wrapper feed
    the unchanged coverage tracker (it reads them off the wrapper).

    Example context (json):
    {
        "playback_id": "abc123",
        "playback_token": "jwt",
        "drm_token": "",
        "drm_required": false,
        "accent_color": "#ec1e5b",
        "no_skip_required": false,
        "activity_name": "Welcome video",
        "activity_id": 1,
        "cm_id": 2,
        "asset_id": 3,
        "session_token": "tok",
        "current_position": 0,
        "asset_duration_seconds": 120,
        "completion_watch_percent": 90,
        "completion_enabled": true,
        "has_completed": false,
        "expires_at_ts": 0,
        "intro_html": "<p>Intro.</p>"
    }
}}
<div class="mod_fastpix-player-wrapper"
     data-region="fastpix-player-wrapper"
     data-cm-id="{{cm_id}}"
     data-activity-id="{{activity_id}}"
     data-asset-id="{{asset_id}}"
     data-session-token="{{session_token}}"
     data-expires-at="{{expires_at_ts}}"
     data-no-skip-required="{{#no_skip_required}}1{{/no_skip_required}}{{^no_skip_required}}0{{/no_skip_required}}"
     data-playback-id="{{playback_id}}"
     data-playback-token="{{playback_token}}"
     data-drm-token="{{drm_token}}"
     data-drm-required="{{#drm_required}}1{{/drm_required}}{{^drm_required}}0{{/drm_required}}"
     data-accent-color="{{accent_color}}"
     data-video-title="{{activity_name}}"
     data-current-position="{{current_position}}"
     data-threshold="{{completion_watch_percent}}"
     data-asset-duration="{{asset_duration_seconds}}">

    <div class="mod_fastpix-status-complete{{#completion_enabled}}{{#has_completed}} is-complete{{/has_completed}}{{/completion_enabled}}"
         data-region="fastpix-status"
         role="status" aria-live="polite">

        <svg class="mod_fastpix-status-svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
             role="img" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 12.5 L10 17.5 L19 7" fill="none" stroke-width="2.5"
                  stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>

        <span class="mod_fastpix-status-label">{{#str}}status_completed, mod_fastpix{{/str}}</span>
    </div>
</div>
{{#intro_html}}
<div class="mod_fastpix-lede">{{{intro_html}}}</div>
{{/intro_html}}
